@Renegator

Okay, but this is not the same as misgendering someone.  Misgendering is referring to somebody as a different gender from how they identify.  But cis means that you identify as the gender you were assigned at birth.  Cis is the word that has been coined to mean exactly that.  

In my experience, when someone says they don't want to be referred to as cis, what they really mean is that they don't want to recognize that people can be born in bodies that don't match how they feel inside.

